content: <?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>  <reference anchor='I-D.zorn-dime-rfc4005bis'> <front> <title>Diameter Network Access Server Application</title>  <author initials='G' surname='Zorn' fullname='Glen Zorn'>     <organization /> </author>  <date month='May' day='23' year='2010' />  <abstract><t>This document describes the Diameter protocol application used for Authentication, Authorization, and Accounting (AAA) services in the Network Access Server (NAS) environment.  When combined with the Diameter Base protocol, Transport Profile, and Extensible Authentication Protocol specifications, this application specification satisfies typical network access services requirements.</t></abstract>  </front>  <seriesInfo name='Internet-Draft' value='draft-zorn-dime-rfc4005bis-01' /> <format type='TXT'         target='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-zorn-dime-rfc4005bis-01.txt' /> </reference>
